(56585, 1934, 56283, 'Basharat', 60, '', 1254203512, 'As per my understanding a group is the pattern of shots on a target, so in theory it can refer to both multiple shots from a single projectile firearm  or a single shot from a shot shell firearm.  \n\nHowever the term pattern is used exclusively when referring to the spread of the projectiles fired from a shotgun.  \n\n[url]http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shotgun_shell[/url]\n\n[url]http://www.firearmsid.com/A_distshotpatt.htm[/url]\n\n[url]http://www.marplerifleandpistolclub.org.uk/general/glossary.htm[/url]\n\nBut i think as long as we all understand each other it does not really matter what terminology is used', 0, 1, '58.181.102.57', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2560, 63941),
