(57115, 1571, 45484, 'AzamAgha44', 668, '', 1254319559, 'I am sorry gentlemen for being so late in replying. Actually I remained (and still am) very busy with a delegation for the last three days. New POF ammo performed flawlessly in the pistol. I then deliberately tested some of my old ammo again with the same mixed results. Three rounds out of 12 FTF with minimum impression on the caps. The ones which did fire had normal inundations on the caps. I also fired off about 70 new rounds with no FTF. I was a little put off by accuracy at 25 meters where I could hit three out of five saucer sized steel plates especially when I compared it with performance of a SIG P226 X Zone pistol with a bull barrel (10 plates in 10 rounds). My overall assessment is that Taurau PT 809 is as an excellant weapon for the price, but can not hold its own against real match grade heavy weights in business.', 0, 1, '203.99.177.91', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2094, 64489);
