(57277, 1941, 56387, 'Skeeter60', 861, '', 1254374259, '@midreestaj\n\nYou are right the desi No 2 ammo is more shiny and the markings on the case head are not sharp.\nThe sealing is done with high grade bitumen to make it as water proof as possible. The primers are water proofed by < Ringing > a die stamps a circle around it flowing metal around it to seal it.\nCRIMPING\nAuto pistols Head space on the case mouth so all auto pistol rounds are not crimped in the classic sense. \nThese are Taper Crimped. If you look at the 9mm round with a mag glass you will see the rim of the case mouth sharp and not bent in wards. In Taper Crimping the last few mm s  of the case length grip the round as these are taperd inwards. \nWhere as the G3 round you can see the mouth of the case bent inwards in a roll crimp as it Head Spaces on the shoulder', 0, 1, '119.154.56.169', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2567, 64686),
