(58257, 1996, 58250, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1254671989, '[quote=Denovo87]Very welldone 12gauge, one thing, is this solvent safe for chromed barrels?[/quote]\n\n\nYes Sir, the solvent is absolutely safe on chromed barrels provided that u do not leave it in the bore for hours at a time and provided that u completely take it off before storing the firearm. the best way to remove any residual ammonia is throughly rinsing the barrel bore with running tap water. afterwards just completely dry the bore and oil it up normally before storing.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. if a person is realy finiky about using water bath then that person can always use/apply kerosene or WD40 after water bath just to displace any water molecules left in the bore. but I feel that this step realy isnt necessary since any good quality gun oil is already a water displacer.', 0, 1, '58.65.151.165', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2640, 65781),
