(62771, 247, 3994, 'StevenCline', 912, '', 1255922127, '[quote=Saeen]Many of us like to carry one in the pipe. Unfortunately not all the handguns out there are safe for that. In your experience which gun implements this feature very efficiently ?.[/quote]\n\nI am sorry, but I blame the person and not the gun.  When you choose to introduce a mechanical restaint preventing you from firing the gun you are also creating a risk that the gun will not go bang when you want it to go bang.  I used to have nightmares about forgetting to flip the decocker on the S&W I carried on the Sheriff''s Department.  When I began carrying a Glock I did not have those nightmares.\n\nNow I carry a 1911.  I don''t have the nightmares because I''ve drawn the 1911 too many times in competitions that I no longer sub-consciously fear I will forget to disengage the thumb safety... but I digress.\n\nTo answer your question:\n\nMy first choice: Any XD (grip safety) or better yet, a Browning HiPower!!!\nMy fist choice for my PakGun friends: A Beretta clone\nOther considerations:\nAny CZ or clone(decocker/safety)\nAny 1911 (grip and thumb safety)\n\nOK, any gun with a thumb safety or decocker, as I presume that it your concern.', 0, 1, '69.155.117.39', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 328, 70745),
