(65600, 212, 3366, 'Mobilinker', 170, '', 1256636577, '@ 12gauge:\n\n1-   Calculation is Theoratical for DAP52 and normal 9mm Parabellum ammo as I mentioned and you also quoted the same.\n\n2-   DAP''s are high both in grain and lead, even the POF SMG IIP round is heavier than their normal IP 9mm round both in terms of weight and grains.\n\n3- When a high velocity and high pressure round goes through the barrel, its damaging effect (colloision, friction) is much higher than a round of lower energy. We all are agreed on it. Hence if the barrel life for DAP round is 9k, its defnintely much more for normal (P) rounds that all of us mostly use in our handguns. Only 9mm P rounds have very less damage to barrel groves as compared to DAP ammunation. I hope this will clear the point.\n\nMoreover, CF98.NP42 have fully supported chambers. While handling +P+ ammo, a Glock may coboom as we''ve seen on net, but CF98.NP42 can not.', 0, 1, '116.71.163.250', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 288, 74042),
